CAPE TOWN - Surfer Bianca Buitendag pocketed South Africa's second medal at the Tokyo Olympics when she finished second in her final on Tuesday. Buitendag picked up the silver medal, Team SA's second for the day after she was defeated 14.93 to 8.46 by the USA's Carissa Marks. The American was the top seed at the Games and is a four-time world champion. Earlier on Tuesday, swimmer Tatjana Schoenmaker picked up the silver medal in the women's 100m breaststroke final. SILVER!!!  Bianca Buitendag takes the silver medal in  womens surfing with gold going to No1 seed and 4x world champion Carissa Marks of the USA 14.93 to 8.46#TeamSA #tokyo2020  Silver Medalist at the first ever Womens Surfing @olympics competition #TeamSA#Olympics#Tokyo2020 #BiancaBuitendag pic.twitter.com/89fJB1dBjW  Congrats Team USA. Thats the 2nd time today youve stood between us and the  https://t.co/P0rhFvWABy  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.